	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thanks for reading,<br /><br />I am looking for a way to play a ROM containing a great translation of FF3j on my actual NES.  513k size.  Will the PowerPak work (I heard there is a 512k limit)?<br /><br />Thanks for your help,<br />Will

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>thefox</b> [ Fri Apr 11, 2014 12:12 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: How to move FF3j translated rom onto a cartridge (PowerP</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Should work. The 16 byte iNES header may make it so that it's displayed as 513 KB somewhere. Besides, PowerPak has a separate 512 KB limit for PRG and CHR, so the maximum supported iNES ROM size is 1 MB.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

